            "sublevel": "intermediate",
            "topic": "Strings — Intermediate Level",
            "theory": "**String slicing** extracts a substring with `[start:stop:step]`:\n`s = 'Python'`\n`s[1:4]` → `'yth'`, `s[::2]` → `'Pto'`, `s[::-1]` → `'nohtyP'`\n\n**f-strings** (f-string literals, Python 3.6+) embed expressions directly:\n`name = 'Alice'; age = 30`\n`f'My name is {name} and I am {age} years old.'`\n\nCommon methods:\n- `.split(sep)` — splits into a list: `'a,b,c'.split(',')` → `['a','b','c']`\n- `','.join(lst)` — joins a list: `','.join(['a','b'])` → `'a,b'`\n- `.find(sub)` — returns index or -1\n- `.startswith(prefix)`, `.endswith(suffix)`\n- `.count(sub)` — counts occurrences",
